column1: Twas bryllig and the slithy toves
did gyre and gimble in the wabe.
Beware the Jubjub bird and shun...
He took his vorpal sword in hand
column2: long time the manxome foe he sought.

column1: So rested he by the Tumtum tree and stood awhile in thought.

column2: as in uffish thought he stood
column3: the Jabberwock with eyes of flame

column1: came whiffling through the Tulgey wood and burbled as it came.
One-two! One-two! And through! And through!
And hast though slain the Jabberwock?
